    description:
      "Enabling LNG Terminals\n\nConnect LNG will enable distribution of cleaner and cheaper energy to the world by commercializing the Universal Buoyancy System (UBS), a buoy solution for LNG transfer between ship and shore. The system enables a much faster installation time, reduces investment costs and reduces investment risk by providing mobile infrastructure compared to the alternative, which is to build a quay or jetty.\n\nThe Connect LNG founders are young people with innovative mindsets from NSE and NTNU Department of Maritime Technology combined with highly experienced people within the oil&gas and maritime industry.\n\nSince the startup in 2012, three model tests have been conducted at NTNU/MARINTEK with great success, and DNV-GL has issued a statement of feasibility for the system. The company is supported by NTNU Discovery, Innovation Norway, Partnere for Nyskaping, and the Norwegian Research Council. The company is experiencing formidable momentum, and has received a lot of international interest.",
